      "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
      "Text": "Data description: https://doi.org/10.25919/mwbk-rj13.\n \nDisclaimer: The creators, contributors, and distributors of the dataset shall not be held liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from the use of the dataset, including but not limited to, inaccuracies, errors, or omissions in the data.\nUnauthorized use or dissemination of this data is prohibited without explicit permission from the data owner. For further inquiries or permission requests, please contact Dr Jeremy Whish (Jeremy.Whish@csiro.au) and John Kirkegaard (John.Kirkegaard@csiro.au).\n \nWhen citing this dataset, please use the following reference: Whish, J., Li, X., Swan, T., Dunn, M., Fiske, K., Pumpa, R., Barary, M., Reardon, D.,  Kirkegaard, J., 2025. Improving farming system efficiency in Southern New South Wales (GRDC 2017-2023). https://doi.org/10.25919/mwbk-rj13.\n\nWhen using the damage functions, please use the following reference for more information: Hu, P., He, D., Zheng, B., Whish, J., Kirkegaard, J., Bell, L., Leske, B., Chen, S., Uppal, R., Biddulph, B., Trethowan, R., Beletse, Y., Lilley, J., 2026. Event-based frost and heat damage functions improve yield predictions of APSIM canola and wheat: formulation, calibration, and evaluation. Agricultural and Forest Meteorology 386, 111239. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.agrformet.2026.111239",
      "Name": "Data Ownership Acknowledgement",
      "ResourceName": null,
      "Children": [],
      "Enabled": true,
      "ReadOnly": false
    },
